IDEAS.md
dexter.txt
run.txt
run2.txt
run3.txt
run4.txt

# Benchmark reports reference local machine paths — keep private
bench/reports/
# Benchmark scripts reference local model paths — internal tooling, keep private
bench/

# ---- Internal working / strategy docs (NOT part of the public product) ----
# Personal context, launch strategy, influencer lists, scavenge notes, internal
# QA prompts. These contain personal data and/or marketing strategy that should
# never be public. The public docs are README / CONTRIBUTING / SECURITY / the
# product docs under docs/ (ARCHITECTURE, USER_GUIDE, RUNBOOK, WAKE_WORD, SUPPORT).
CLAUDE.md
PUBLISH.md
LAUNCH-DAY.md
docs/MARKETING.md
docs/LAUNCH_POSTS.md
docs/SCAVENGE.md
docs/DEMO_SCRIPT.md
docs/TEST_PLAYBOOK*.md
docs/RUNBOOK.md

# ---- Stale deep docs — deferred until rewritten post-launch ----
# The codebase moved fast; these describe an older Hearth and would ship wrong
# info. Better to ship fewer accurate docs (README + docs/TOOLS.md + CHANGELOG)
# than stale ones. Remove from this list once they're brought up to date.
docs/ARCHITECTURE.md
docs/WAKE_WORD.md

# ---- Local-only build artefacts ----
# graphify knowledge-graph outputs (regenerate with scripts/run_graphify_on_hearth.py)
graphify-out/
# per-provider API keys saved by /brain command — contains plaintext secrets
brain_keys.json
# large reference PDF used for the map-reduce subagent demo
Timelines of History*.pdf
